{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NJVB1Z8TPZZe7S1HCd66mK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the problem clearly now. The `elasticsearch.yml` configmap is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. This is required for a brand-new Elasticsearch cluster to bootstrap itself. Without it, the nodes can't elect a master for the first time.\n\nThe `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting is needed for the initial cluster bootstrapping. The nodes all have role `master`, and without this setting, they cannot form the initial quorum.\n\nThe fix is:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap so the cluster can bootstrap\n2. After the cluster forms successfully, remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` (because it's a bootstrap-only setting and should not be present after the cluster is formed, to avoid split-brain scenarios on future restarts)\n3. Restart the pods to apply the config change, wait for the cluster to form with a master elected, then remove the bootstrap setting and do a rolling restart to verify stability.\n\nLet me look at how the StatefulSet is configured to understand the pod setup better.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":512,"cache_read_input_tokens":34034,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":512},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0715adff-902c-41dc-a396-8ac05bd18717","uuid":"a6e47f7f-cfd1-453e-acac-1f4546036b0d","request_id":"req_011CcgFC3e3bfEf5i4KjUXNs"}
