{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012S8KXSnytHDXsdwGQDLMYS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear: `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is missing from `elasticsearch.yml`, so the nodes can't bootstrap and elect a master. The plan:\n\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap\n2. Restart pods to pick up new config (subPath mounts don't auto-update)\n3. Wait for cluster to form (green/yellow)\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` (bootstrap-only setting)\n5. Rolling restart to verify cluster stays healthy without it\n\n**Step 1: Patch the ConfigMap with the bootstrap setting.**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1906,"cache_read_input_tokens":34546,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1906},"output_tokens":39,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0715adff-902c-41dc-a396-8ac05bd18717","uuid":"aa64f6f4-0cd6-4c0b-8e59-2e25a42734ee","request_id":"req_011CcgFCzr9B6GuAFGGvQbxA"}
