{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MXTNvM5H8oiky1LWfSi5Xm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are achieved. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-config` ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which Elasticsearch 7.x requires for the very first cluster bootstrap. Without it, nodes can't form a quorum to elect a master.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** to the ConfigMap — lists all 3 nodes so any quorum of them can bootstrap the cluster.\n\n2. **Restarted all 3 pods** — required because the config is mounted as a `subPath` volume, which doesn't auto-refresh when the ConfigMap changes.\n\n3. **Cluster formed**: green, 3 nodes, master elected (`es-cluster-2` → later `es-cluster-1` after rolling restart).\n\n4. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** from the ConfigMap — this setting is bootstrap-only. Leaving it in place after the cluster forms is dangerous: on a future full restart it could trigger a new bootstrap election and ignore the stored cluster state, risking split-brain.\n\n5. **Rolling restart** (one pod at a time, waiting for green+3 nodes before proceeding): cluster remained green throughout and all three nodes restarted cleanly without the bootstrap setting.\n\n**Final state:** green, 3 nodes, master elected (`es-cluster-1`), `cluster.initial_master_nodes` absent from config."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2624,"cache_read_input_tokens":40347,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2624},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0715adff-902c-41dc-a396-8ac05bd18717","uuid":"6d0ca604-9541-4dfd-9292-83bd9136db4c","request_id":"req_011CcgFmq9uTrgEkrfNroZfF"}
